==English==
===Etymology===
From the story of [[w:Cinderella]], where the transformed coach reverts back to its original state (that of a pumpkin) at midnight.

===Verb===
'''[[turn]] [[into]] [[a]] [[pumpkin]]'''
# {{idiom}} ''[[Colloquial]]'' To go to [[bed]]; to go to [[sleep]] (especially at, or around [[midnight]].)
#:''I'm about ready to '''turn into a pumpkin'''.  You can stay up later if you want.''
#:''Tell her I'm '''turning into a pumpkin''' if she stays out too late. She won't be getting a lift from me.''